<span id="freeTextContainer5462173639367965241"><br/>This is my favorite Carol Shields book so far, and that is saying a lot because I adore Carol Shields. This novel was short-listed for the Booker. There is so much here, but it is portrayed in the classic slow, sensitive, Shieldsian manner. Those who think there is &quot;nothing going on here&quot; or that it&apos;s &quot;too slow&quot; or &quot;boring&quot; are most certainly missing a great deal. This novel invites a second or third read as well.</span>
  <span id="freeText5462173639367965241" style="display:none"><br />This is my favorite Carol Shields book so far, and that is saying a lot because I adore Carol Shields. This novel was short-listed for the Booker. There is so much here, but it is portrayed in the classic slow, sensitive, Shieldsian manner. Those who think there is "nothing going on here" or that it's "too slow" or "boring" are most certainly missing a great deal. This novel invites a second or third read as well.</span>
