<span id="freeTextContainer10342269416286236442">The novel I wish I&apos;d written. <br/><br/>So many times in the book I thought &quot;YES!&quot; and &quot;Well put!&quot; and &quot;Why can&apos;t I articulate like Carol Shields!? This is exactly how I feel!&quot;<br/><br/>I loved this book, which I ignored for many years for some reason. No idea why, as I loved <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/77554.The_Stone_Diaries' title='The Stone Diaries by Carol Shields' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Stone Diaries</a>. While this one is different, it is equally as beautiful, and even more intellectual and precise. This is a book I&apos;ll save for my daughter, and one that I wish my husband could read, but I doubt he&apos;d get it, which is, of cour</span>
  <span id="freeText10342269416286236442" style="display:none">The novel I wish I'd written. <br /><br />So many times in the book I thought "YES!" and "Well put!" and "Why can't I articulate like Carol Shields!? This is exactly how I feel!"<br /><br />I loved this book, which I ignored for many years for some reason. No idea why, as I loved <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/77554.The_Stone_Diaries" title="The Stone Diaries by Carol Shields" rel="nofollow noopener">The Stone Diaries</a>. While this one is different, it is equally as beautiful, and even more intellectual and precise. This is a book I'll save for my daughter, and one that I wish my husband could read, but I doubt he'd get it, which is, of course, the irony of the book itself!<br /><br />I kept thinking of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/270543.Elizabeth_Hay" title="Elizabeth Hay" rel="nofollow noopener">Elizabeth Hay</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/46051.Rachel_Cusk" title="Rachel Cusk" rel="nofollow noopener">Rachel Cusk</a> as I read <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/74462.Unless" title="Unless by Carol Shields" rel="nofollow noopener">Unless</a>. These are two similar authors that I have loved, and would recommend to readers who enjoyed this book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10342269416286236442" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


