<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer2613746625388166628">Carol Ann Shields was an American-born Canadian author. She is best known for her successful 1993 novel <i>The Stone Diaries</i>, which won the Pulitzer Prize for Fiction as well as the Governor General&apos;s Award. Her novel <i>Swann</i> won the Best Novel <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/award/show/1066-arthur-ellis-award' rel='nofollow noopener'>Arthur Ellis Award</a> in 1988.<br/><br/><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText2613746625388166628" style="display:none">Carol Ann Shields was an American-born Canadian author. She is best known for her successful 1993 novel <i>The Stone Diaries</i>, which won the Pulitzer Prize for Fiction as well as the Governor General's Award. Her novel <i>Swann</i> won the Best Novel <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/award/show/1066-arthur-ellis-award" rel="nofollow noopener">Arthur Ellis Award</a> in 1988.<br /><br /><br /></span>
